IRS990.MissionDesc: FINGER LAKES PERFORMING PROVIDER SYSTEM, INC. ("FLPPS") WAS RESPONSIBLE FOR IMPLEMENTATION OF THE NYS DELIVERY SYSTEM REFORM INCENTIVE PAYMENT ("DSRIP") PROGRAM FROM 2015-2020 AND NOW CONTINUES TO REDESIGN THE HEALTHCARE DELIVERY SYSTEM IN THE 13-COUNTY REGION. ORIGINALLY CREATED UNDER THE NYS 1115 WAIVER, THE OVERALL OBJECTIVE OF FLPPS IS TO TRANSFORM THE HEALTHCARE DELIVERY SYSTEM AND IMPROVE HEALTH OUTCOMES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION HAS TWO CORPORATE MEMBERS WHO EACH HAVE A 50% INTEREST. THE MEMBERS ARE ROCHESTER REGIONAL HEALTH AND THE UNIVERSITY OF ROCHESTER.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CORPORATION SHALL HAVE TWO CORPORATE MEMBERS. THESE MEMBERS SHALL BE RU SYSTEM, INC. AND THE UNIVERSITY OF ROCHESTER (EACH INDIVIDUALLY BEING A "MEMBER AND COLLECTIVELY REFERRED HEREIN TO AS THE "MEMBERS"). EACH MEMBER SHALL DESIGNATE ONE OR MORE REPRESENTATIVES TO ATTEND MEETINGS AND OTHERWISE ACT ON ITS BEHALF. REGARDLESS OF THE NUMBER OF REPRESENTATIVES IT DESIGNATES, EACH MEMBER SHALL HAVE ONE (1) VOTE ON ALL MATTERS REQUIRING MEMBERSHIP ACTION. BOTH MEMBERS ARE 501(C)3 ORGANIZATIONS. THE MEMBERS SHALL HAVE AND EXERCISE ANY AND ALL RIGHTS AND POWERS OF CORPORATE MEMBERSHIP CREATED BY THE LAWS OF THE STATE OF NEW YORK OR THE CERTIFICATE OF INCORPORATION OR BYLAWS OF THE CORPORATION. ADDITIONALLY, THE MEMBERS POSSESS CERTAIN GOVERNANCE AND MANAGEMENT POWERS. AS OUTLINED IN THE ARTICLES OF INCORPORATION AND BYLAWS. THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS IS APPOINTED BY THE MEMBERS AT THE ANNUAL MEETING. THE BYLAWS OUTLINE CERTAIN REQUIREMENTS REGARDING THE NUMBER AND TYPE OF DIRECTORS THAT MUST BE APPOINTED TO THE BOARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE ORGANIZATION REQUIRE A UNANIMOUS VOTE OF THE MEMBERS AT A DULY CONVENED MEETING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS MADE AVAILABLE TO THE BOARD MEMBERS PRIOR TO FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: WRITTEN CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICIES ARE REVIEWED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. CONFLICT OF INTEREST DISCLOSURE STATEMENTS ARE REQUIRED TO BE COMPLETED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ANNUALLY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMPENSATION OF OFFICERS IS APPROVED BY THE BOARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 18
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ORGANIZATIONAL DOCUMENTS TO THE ORGANIZATION IS AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST TO THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: INFORMATION RELATED TO THE ORGANIZATION IS AVAILABLE THROUGH THE DIRECTOR OF FINANCE AND THE WEBSITE OF THE ENTITY, FLPPS.ORG.
